#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn1.19"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.19:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.19:0.2"
msgid "2. Nandanavagga "
msgstr "2. The Garden of Delight "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.19:0.3"
msgid "19. Kuṭikāsutta "
msgstr "19. Little Hut "

#. HTML: </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.8, pts2ed1.17, sc1
msgctxt "sn1.19:1.1"
msgid "“Kacci te kuṭikā natthi, "
msgstr "“Don’t you have a little hut? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:1.2"
msgid "kacci natthi kulāvakā; "
msgstr "Don’t you have a little nest? "

# NOTE: I’m not exactly sure what this means here. Elsewhere in AN and SN santaka means “a network (of roots)”. In the Vinaya it apparently means “cobwebs” (or might it also meaning"overgrowing creepers?)
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:1.3"
msgid "Kacci santānakā natthi, "
msgstr "Don’t you have any networks? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:1.4"
msgid "kacci muttosi bandhanā”ti. "
msgstr "Aren’t you free of shackles?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn1.19:2.1"
msgid "“Taggha me kuṭikā natthi, "
msgstr "“Indeed I have no little hut. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:2.2"
msgid "taggha natthi kulāvakā; "
msgstr "Indeed I have no little nest. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:2.3"
msgid "Taggha santānakā natthi, "
msgstr "Indeed I have no networks. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:2.4"
msgid "taggha muttomhi bandhanā”ti. "
msgstr "Indeed I’m free from shackles.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn1.19:3.1"
msgid "“Kintāhaṃ kuṭikaṃ brūmi, "
msgstr "“What do you think I call a little hut? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:3.2"
msgid "kiṃ te brūmi kulāvakaṃ; "
msgstr "What do I call a little nest? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:3.3"
msgid "Kiṃ te santānakaṃ brūmi, "
msgstr "What do you think I call a network? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:3.4"
msgid "kintāhaṃ brūmi bandhanan”ti. "
msgstr "And what do I call a shackle?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.18, sc4
msgctxt "sn1.19:4.1"
msgid "“Mātaraṃ kuṭikaṃ brūsi, "
msgstr "“You call a mother a little hut; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:4.2"
msgid "bhariyaṃ brūsi kulāvakaṃ; "
msgstr "and a wife a little nest. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:4.3"
msgid "Putte santānake brūsi, "
msgstr "You call children a network, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:4.4"
msgid "taṇhaṃ me brūsi bandhanan”ti. "
msgstr "and you tell me craving’s a shackle.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn1.19:5.1"
msgid "“Sāhu te kuṭikā natthi, "
msgstr "“It’s good you have no little hut! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:5.2"
msgid "sāhu natthi kulāvakā; "
msgstr "It’s good you have no little nest! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:5.3"
msgid "Sāhu santānakā natthi, "
msgstr "It’s good you have no networks! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.19:5.4"
msgid "sāhu muttosi bandhanā”ti. "
msgstr "And good that you’re free from shackles.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
